<subSubSection id="9AE63F9389A347C7F2E5B1F4F1CE42BF" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="0805ED6696DBE7F06F5A7B6F9698FF5C" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E1855794F2A5CF4FD9A6B1E6E8494F4" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
Thailand, Chiang Rai, Wat Phra That Doi Tung (Temple of Doi Tung Pagodas), the host 
<taxonomicName id="7D62DA82406D6AC6E779C78C8AFA8C11" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Dendrobium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dendrobium" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Dendrobium</taxonomicName>
sp. 2 was collected on 19 December 2013, Collector: Sureeporn Nontachaiyapoom, Natdanai Aewsakul, Xiaoya Ma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9797EC654D198EEF78A7A8511166DA8E" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" type="notes">
<paragraph id="1B0FB5AD5DE50578E5D0A641EFF44D77" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E80FDF608C71EAB13082883C2EEDCE6" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName id="F526E481B2657D31408299501B9D119F" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Glomerellaceae" genus="Colletotrichum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Colletotrichum doitungense" order="Glomerellales" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="doitungense">Colletotrichum doitungense</taxonomicName>
form an independent lineage from other strains with good support (66ML/1.00BI/73MP) in 
<taxonomicName id="CAE76B90AB5A0C7B5F9317B4BDCEA9E9" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Glomerellaceae" genus="Colletotrichum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Colletotrichum boninense" order="Glomerellales" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="boninense">boninense</taxonomicName>
species complex. The ITS sequence of MFLUCC 14-0128 100% matches with unpublished pathogenic 
<taxonomicName id="8C2E79FF4E95CC4E146D3825B1301D8F" genus="C." lsidName="C. cymbidiicola" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="cymbidiicola">C. cymbidiicola</taxonomicName>
strain OORC18 (GenBank JX902424) isolated from orchid in India and 
<taxonomicName id="FDA349987FA556E280351EB39B0698B1" genus="C." lsidName="C. karstii" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="karstii">C. karstii</taxonomicName>
strain R001 (GenBank JN715846) isolated from blackberry in Colombia (Unpublished). Blastn researches with sequences of MFLUCC 14-0128 results in 98% identity with GAPDH sequence of endophytic 
<taxonomicName id="AA52E0F5BDFB6A9E12BBD78D50CB05A9" genus="C." lsidName="C. boninense" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="boninense">C. boninense</taxonomicName>
strain CGMCC 3.15168 (GenBank KC843491) isolated from 
<taxonomicName id="E52B67AAD310C1B7589D0D67C10EB412" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bletilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bletilla ochracea" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ochracea">Bletilla ochracea</taxonomicName>
in China (
<bibRefCitation id="3FFB45FEC90BF9E34F5746B231D4B535" author="Tao, G" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" pagination="139 - 164" title="Endophytic Colletotrichum species from Bletillaochracea (Orchidaceae) with descriptions of seven new species." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-013-0254-5" volume="61" year="2013">Tao et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
), 99% identity with ACT sequence of 
<taxonomicName id="EA440B4AC546F1D3C78D4D8AD7E06B69" genus="C." lsidName="C. boninense" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="boninense">C. boninense</taxonomicName>
strain CBS 125502 (GenBank KJ954462) and 99% identity with TUB2 sequence of 
<taxonomicName id="54D1F4CADA37D72C559880D77B7DB8BD" genus="C." lsidName="C. citricola" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="citricola">C. citricola</taxonomicName>
strain SXC 151 (GenBank KC293656) as mentioned above. Its conidiogenus cell is globose to sub-globose, which differ from cylindrical to ellipsoidal conidiogenus cell in 
<taxonomicName id="70C585D0DE138354853EDA9D335FBBEF" genus="C." lsidName="C. boninense" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="boninense">C. boninense</taxonomicName>
(Damm et al. 2012). This strain has 2 and 0 in ITS, 6 and 1 in GAPDH, 3 and 2 in ACT, 17 and 16 base pair differences from its sister taxon 
<taxonomicName id="0668F29D64CEA7910F77416F25B19A52" genus="C." lsidName="C. torulosum" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="torulosum">C. torulosum</taxonomicName>
and MFLUCC 14-0261 respectively. Here we introduce 
<taxonomicName id="1AD48654BEEE6D5F6D7383011172E5F6" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Glomerellaceae" genus="Colletotrichum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Colletotrichum doitungense" order="Glomerellales" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="doitungense">Colletotrichum doitungense</taxonomicName>
isolated from root of 
<taxonomicName id="A9F9258B9875E1D163D81528D47F0049" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Dendrobium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dendrobium" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Dendrobium</taxonomicName>
sp. 2 as a new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
